>> servings: 3

Prepare the marinade in a big bowl: @cumin{1%tsp}, minced @garlic{4%tsp}, @oregano{1%tsp}, @salt{2%tsp}, @black pepper{1%tsp}, @chilli powder{1%tbsp}, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @canned tomatoes{200%g}, and @chipotle powder{2%tsp}. Whisk to combine and taste to adjust seasoning.

Put the @chicken thighs{6} in the marinade and make sure every slice is covered with it. Leave in fridge ~{overnight}.

Add some oil to create an even coating on the pan. Fry the chicken thighs for ~{5 minutes} on each side. Optional: add salt to season.
